The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining dynamic matrices, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The main problem addressed in the paper is fully dynamic transitive closure, which is a classic problem in graph algorithms and can be categorized under computational geometry (cs.CG), combinatorics (cs.DM), and complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of polynomials in the algorithm, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and machine learning (cs.LG).
